Debriefing: 
The purpose of this study was to replicate the research done by Ohtsubo et al. (2014). In this 
study, we were specifically replicating the claim by Ohtsubo that a partner’s attention toward a 
target person would increase the target’s intimacy with the partner. To do this, we told you that 
you would be interacting with another peer. Instead, you were the only participant in this study. 
Half of the participants had the peer observing light activate 80% of the time – the other half of 
the participants did not have the light activate at all. The results of this study will be aggregated 
with 299 other similar studies being run at different universities throughout the world. The 
results of these studies will be combined with expert predictions of what studies will replicate 
(and what studies will not) in attempt to allow for the accurate prediction of what studies can be 
