Sample size 
The target analytic sample size is 40 participants. This is based on the phase one power analysis 
(my lab ran the Phase One study for Score - this was the sum total of participants to achieve the 
target power). 
 
Data collection will continue until 40 usable participants are collected. As noted below, 
participants will be excluded for failing the suspicion probe (where participants indicate 
suspicion about the true nature of the study). These will be the only exclusions. 

Sample size rationale 
This is based on the phase one power analysis (my lab ran the Phase One study for Score - this 
was the sum total of participants to achieve the target power). 
Stopping rule 
The planned sample size is 40. After achieving this sample, sampling will stop and planned 
analyses will be run. Exclusions will be made as the study is ongoing due to suspicion. 
Variables 
Manipulated variables 
The manipulated variable in this study is attention from the partner, operationalized as the 
zoom camera being on.  
 
There are 2 levels: “attention”, one where the partner (RA) has the camera on and one where 
the camera is off.  
 
No files selected 
Measured variables 
The focal measured variable for this replication is the intimacy score, which is an index of 4 
questions.  Those questions are: 
1)    If you became friends with the partner, how well do you think this person would 
understand you? 
2)    If you became friends with your partner, how much do you think this person would accept 
you? 
3)    How much did the partner care for you? 
4)    How much do you agree that this partner had little concern for you? (reverse coded) 
 
Each is answered on a 1-to-7-point scale (1 = not at all, 7 = very much). 
These four items will then be aggregated as the intimacy score. 
 
We will also collect two items that assess the participant’s interest in being friends with the 
partner to maintain similarity with the original study.  These questions will not be analyzed for 
the focal test. 
1)    How much are you interested in being friends with the partner? 
2)    How much do you agree that the partner and you will be good friends? 
 
Each is answered on a 1-to-7-point scale (1 = not at all, 7 = very much). 
These two items will then be aggregated as the friendship score. 
 
 

We will also collect basic demographics (age, sex, race). 
 
No files selected 
Indices 
There is one index, the intimacy scale, which is the aggregate of the four questions defined in 
the measured variables section.  These scores will be added together, keeping in mind that one 
question is reverse coded. 
 
These scores will then be averaged by condition to perform the focal test. 
 
As a subsidiary analysis, the friendship scale, which is the aggregate of the two friendship 
questions defined in the measured variables section.  These scores will be added together. 
 
No files selected 
Analysis Plan 
Statistical models 
The focal test will be an independent samples t-test comparing the mean intimacy score of the 
“attention” condition to the mean intimacy score of the “no attention” condition. 
 
The subsidiary test will be an independent samples t-test comparing the mean friendship score 
of the “attention” condition to the mean intimacy score of the “no attention” condition. 
 
Finally, an exploratory ANOVA will be done using sex and condition as Ivs with the intimacy 
scores as the DV.  If the sample sizes of males and females is significantly unbalanced (10 or 
less of a category), this analysis will not be performed.  
 
No files selected 
Transformations 
The intimacy score is the summation of the four intimacy questions as detailed in the measured 
variables section. 
Inference criteria 
Criteria for a successful replication attempt for the SCORE project is a statistically significant 
effect (alpha = .05, two tailed) in the same pattern as the original study. For this replication 
attempt, this criteria is met by the average intimacy score for the “attention” condition being 
significantly larger than the average intimacy score for the “no attention” condition. 
Data exclusion 

The only exclusions will occur prior to any analyses being conducted based on the suspicion 
probe. Any participants who suspect the true purpose of the study will be excluded from the 
analyses. 
Missing data 
In the unlikely event of missing data, participant’s data will be excluded from the analysis. 
Exploratory analysis 
As stated earlier, a parallel set of analyses will be done using the friendship index along with 
sex. 
Other 
Other 
Participants will be paid in USD (as opposed to Yen) given that the researcher for the replication 
is based in the US. It is thought that this will not have any impact on the replication. 
 
Additionally, participants will actually see the confederate (potentially introducing variables of 
gender and attractiveness). However, the RA will remain the same for all participants holding 
these variables constant (allowing the manipulation to cleanly have an effect). 
 

